class Solution {
public:
    bool canChange(string start, string target) {
        int n = start.length();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (start[i] != target[i]) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution checks if all characters in the start string are equal to the corresponding characters in the target string. If any mismatch is found, it immediately returns false. Otherwise, it returns true, indicating that the target string can be obtained from the start string. The time complexity is O(n) because the algorithm iterates through the strings once, and the space complexity is O(1) as the algorithm uses a constant amount of space. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few operations and does not consume significant energy.

